<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="455">Diagnosis Unique, distinguished in the major by the very small size; circular head shape in full-face view; eyes set far forward in the head; raised promesonotum that drops through a long, steep face to the metanotum; conate postpetiole; restriction of carinulae to the frontal lobes and antennal fossae; and completely foveolate head and mesosoma. Minor: unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="455">Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.64, HL 0.64, SL 0.34, EL 0.12, PW 0.32. Color Major: dark yellow, with gaster a shade darker of brownish yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="455">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="455">Biology The type specimen was collected from a &quot;red rotten&quot; log on the floor of terra firme forest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
